content:
I don’t agree with Pelosi on much, but we find common ground on this. I’ve been calling to remove the SALT deduction cap for the past 3 years -- it unfairly hurts California taxpayers. Congress should take this up as a clean bill to give taxpayers relief.
https://t.co/GZCKfmbH1P

As our region sees more infections from the coronavirus, we all must continue to do our part. We are here for each other and are all in this together. A special thank you to all of our healthcare professionals risking their lives to keep us safe. https://t.co/jSOnhZNeR1

Huge thanks to the @USNavy.
Having the #USNSMercy up and running is a real help for our medical first responders! 
https://t.co/6LQCru2yUE

In our current situation, international coordination to combat the coronavirus is essential. It's important to learn best practices from those governments who have most successfully responded to this health challenge. At the top of this list is Taiwan. https://t.co/YIWyqm2isP
The effectiveness of the Taiwanese response is all the more impressive given that it’s not a member of the World Health Organization. The world can learn from Taiwan.

It’s impossible to predict when a crisis will strike. In the State Assembly, I co-authored a bill that would have made 3 mobile field hospitals ready for deployment in times like this. Let’s make sure we’re prepared for the next national emergency. https://t.co/rCb7YfU9SB

COVID-19 testing sites are now open in LA County, including one at the Pomona Fairplex. Testing is by appointment only for residents of LA County who are at high-risk and most vulnerable. Please visit https://t.co/ij4kmN94wh for more information.

While talking to people across #CA39 I have continued to receive questions about resources for families, businesses, how to give back & so much more. To address these questions our campaign has put together an info page on our website. Check it out here: https://t.co/wY27RSeK4a https://t.co/DKSj9wMhjW

If you are exposed to #COVID19 it's important to take the necessary precautions to avoid infecting the rest of your household:
1. Prepare in advance
2. Isolate 
3. Cover up and disinfect
4. Keep everyone else from getting sick
https://t.co/wjuVz2y4az

Finding affordable housing in California is hard enough as it is. Adding the pressure of a global pandemic is bringing many California families to the breaking point. Thankfully, many banks are lending a hand.
https://t.co/gbsNCSbjYC

We owe the volunteers stepping up to help our healthcare professionals a great deal of thanks. Your experience is invaluable in a time like this. 
Interested in volunteering & have previous experience in medicine? Volunteer here ➡️ https://t.co/qNz1JIXqQp
https://t.co/9UY8FmeCW4

In these turbulent times so many people in our community are hurting. Our local food banks need help more than ever. If you can, please consider supporting the organizations below.

https://t.co/7l6xp0MMV3 https://t.co/BNDhYelqcP https://t.co/n3RqI3CThs 
https://t.co/mWnvEgjw3D https://t.co/DA9wsuJXyM

“During this uncertain and challenging time for all of us, I want to do what I can to help reassure the community that they are not alone.” Thank you Imran and Khan Saab Desi Craft Kitchen for supporting those in our community who need it most.
https://t.co/x1fosHRnWc

Over the past few weeks, many individuals, businesses & organizations have reached out looking to donate or receive supplies. Our campaign has worked to get thousand of masks, PPE & other supplies to first responders, local hospitals, and those in need. https://t.co/qGya9a8omE

If you or someone you know needs help connecting with an organization, hospital, or agency in order to donate supplies please reach out to us at info@youngkimforcongress.com. All of us doing our small part makes a difference for those impacted by this virus. #CA39
Wishing all our friends celebrating the beginning of Passover a happy holiday! I hope this time brings peace and joy to all.

When so many are struggling, it's heartwarming to see our community come together.
https://t.co/CTOYYIN1mh

OCIE SBDC has created a crisis hotline to provide no cost, direct support with disaster loan applications, cash flow concerns, recovering sales online, tax assistance and work sharing programs. All with the goal of keeping small business doors open.
https://t.co/FW2T3NTtXZ

#ICYMI: We are facing something uniquely challenging with #COVID19 and learning from successful responses is essential. At the top of this list is Taiwan. Check out my full op-ed in the @EpochTimes 
https://t.co/INsPzoQU7j

Our healthcare workers are fighting to keep us healthy, but shouldn’t have to do so without the proper protection. If you have any spare resources or medical supplies you can donate, consider helping hospitals here in Southern California.
https://t.co/UrU5WsDqhR

Charles & I joined our fellow Rotarians today assembling face shields for our courageous frontline healthcare workers. Volunteers assembled thousands of masks. People are needed to assemble thousands more. If you are healthy & interested please visit➡️ https://t.co/RvUMFQJKTl https://t.co/0yQzyRg8S5

#HappyEaster! As Christians celebrate the resurrection of Jesus in this difficult season, I hope we can all encourage one another and choose to be a blessing to those around us. https://t.co/7VHRAwt71K

To the truck drivers, grocery store employees, infrastructure workers, farmers, and everyone still going to work -- thank you for keeping our country moving forward while we fight #COVID19. https://t.co/uLwFxDocU6

Congress and the President must come together now to get needed support to our families, businesses, and hospitals. This isn't a time for partisan bickering or score settling. Our community is hurting and we need leadership that puts people first. #CA39 https://t.co/tXLq66cYG5

@csuf's dance team is adapting to the new normal by hosting online auditions! With resilience and determination, anything can be accomplished.

https://t.co/TAVe3dFpS2
Our campaign is built to win and is continuing to gain momentum. Thank you to everyone that have donated, volunteered and supported us. #CA39 https://t.co/1TLabBdIEL

So many jobs and families in #CA39 are at risk during this crisis. The people of Orange, LA & San Bernardino Countys deserve swift bipartisan action that will address their needs. Our leaders must come together & put people first.
https://t.co/GmpIyz5jsb

Our campaign is built to win and is continuing to gain momentum. Thank you to everyone that has donated, volunteered and supported us. It's time to have a proven independent voice representing #CA39 and with your continued support we will. https://t.co/1TLabBdIEL

Young Kim named as top Republican candidate after finishing ahead of incumbent Gil Cisneros in March primary election.

https://t.co/RvfgcCLQW8

There is a critical need for blood donations during this coronavirus outbreak. Richard Nixon Library is hosting a blood drive tomorrow, April 16th and another one in May. Please considering donating if you can. https://t.co/fyOXX4SriO
